  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.3.8+commit.046ea166\r\n* OS: OSX\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.8.0\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe `__init__` function can be decorated with any mutability or visibility decorator.\r\n\r\n- Regarding visibility, compiling a contract with an `internal` constructor will succeed but when trying to deploy the contract, `brownie` and `web3.py` fails with respectively `VirtualMachineError: stack underflow` and `eth.exceptions.InsufficientStack: Wanted 1 stack item as int, had none`.\r\n```Vyper\r\na:uint256\r\n@internal\r\ndef __init__():\r\n    self.a = 1\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Regarding mutability, it seems to me that it would be useless to have a `view` or a `pure` constructor as the whole goal of a constructor is to have side effects on the contract's state since it cannot return anything. Note that it is however currently possible to have a constructor assigning immutables with a `view` or a `pure` mutability (the following contract compiles).\r\n```Vyper\r\na:immutable(uint256)\r\n@external\r\n@pure\r\ndef __init__():\r\n    a = 1\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nPrevent the `__init__` function to have any decorator except for `external`,`payable` and `nonpayable`.\r\n",
